A Verulam resident was found stabbed to death after an alleged altercation with his stepson in their home in Trenance Park on Friday, 11 March.  It is believed the victim, 48-year-old Dilo Subramoney Pillay, was repeatedly stabbed and two suspects were involved in the murder. A resident from the area contacted Reaction Unit South Africa (RUSA) requesting assistance for the critically injured man. RUSA spokesperson, Prem Balram said reaction officers and RUSA paramedics were immediately dispatched and on arrival were directed into the residence. He said the victim was located lying in a pool of blood in the passage. “Upon examination, he was found to have sustained twelve stab wounds around his body including his back, chest and face. He showed no signs of life and was declared deceased.” Balram alleged that the deceased and his wife were involved in an argument when his stepson intervened. “During the altercation the deceased was repeatedly stabbed. His stepson fled but later returned while first responders were attending to the scene. His clothing was drenched in blood. The suspect, estimated to be in his early 20’s, was placed under arrest by police and detained by Verulam SAPS.” KwaZulu-Natal SAPS spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala, said: “We can confirm the incident that took place on 11 March at Trenance Park in Verulam where a 48-year-old man was allegedly stabbed to death by two known suspects. A 24-year-old man and a 43-year-old woman were arrested by Verulam police for murder and they are expected to appear in the Verulam Magistrate’s Court. The motive for the killing is unknown.”